<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="iddd25a09e-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee" identifier="/us/usc/t2/s4913"><num value="4913">§ 4913.</num><heading> Regulations of Page Board</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Page Board shall have authority to prescribe such regulations as may be necessary to carry out sections 4911 to 4913 of this title.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="iddd25a09f-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee">(<ref href="/us/pl/97/377/tI/s127">Pub. L. 97–377, title I, § 127</ref>, <date date="1982-12-21">Dec. 21, 1982</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/96/1914">96 Stat. 1914</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="iddd25a0a0-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="iddd25a0a1-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="iddd25a0a2-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was formerly classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t2/s88b–4">section 88b–4 of this title</ref> prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section is based on section 3 of House Resolution No. 611, Ninety-seventh Congress, <date date="1982-11-30">Nov. 30, 1982</date>, which was enacted into permanent law by <ref href="/us/pl/97/377">Pub. L. 97–377</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
